<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Puissant" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Puissant,</orth> mighty, powerful: <cit><quote>with your p. arm renew their feats,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.116" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 116</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my thrice p. liege,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.116" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 116</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>trailest thou the p. pike?</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 40</bibl></cit> (Pistol's speech). <cit><quote>with a p. and a mighty power,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.9.25" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 9, 25</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with a p. host,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.207" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 207</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.2.31" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 31</bibl>. <cit><quote>a p. navy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.434" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 434</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>most high, most mighty, and most p. Caesar,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 1, 33</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his grief grew p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.216" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 216</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>